@Reasoning:
Class symbols are currently aliased to their declaring AST node -
the AST node already carries name, modifiers, type parameters,
members, supertypes, and source location, which is everything the
resolver and later phases need. Using the AST identity as the symbol
avoids duplicating storage and keeps "is this the same class?"
queries pointer-equal.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns class_node unchanged. Callers store the result into
global_scope under the class name.
@End Implementation
