@Reasoning:
Static type inference for an arbitrary expression. Used by null-
safety checks to determine whether a target expression is nullable.
The full inference algorithm needs the resolved type environment and
specific rules per expression kind (literals, member access, calls,
lambdas, etc.). Currently returns 0 which the null-safety callers
interpret as "no type info available, skip the warning" - safe
default that does not cause false positives.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Returns 0. The full inference algorithm will read expr's type tag,
recursively infer subexpression types, and consult the analyzer's
type_system; that work lives in the type-inference work-stream and
its results will be wired in here once available.
@End Implementation
